{"author":{"id":"2f476296e781991c88f7df7186275ff8937aed65fb5b8fd0844af3324a17691b"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1706266564,"nonce":"jzDpb+D5sLHT+Ep+JIhI3nK2KOc=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOJl1IZM59SixPzlLX-M8"},"target":"b562f1de10a57ace1c970ce44bcade4ce9f4dea8f5f6bf1dcc4a90df37e4f255","message":"I am not sure to call it an \"issue\", but I rather wanted to try to help other users who face this...\n\nSince the screen recorder app \"[Kap](https://getkap.co/)\" is detected as a new window it get's applied to the current layout. Therefor it can (especially when using `tiles`) get hardly possible to screen capture properly, since Kap is designed to overlay on top of all current windows and the user should define an area/window/fullscreen to capture.\nSo f.e. it can look something like this:\n![image](https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/assets/24993816/260b6553-41c6-4670-80c6-93c50af128fb)\n\nWorkaround that work's for me: adding `[[on-window-detected]]` rule\n```toml\n[[on-window-detected]]\nif.app-id = 'com.wulkano.kap'\nrun = 'layout floating'\n```\n\n\n- AeroSpace version: 0.8.2-Beta\n- macOS version: 14.2.1","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1706266717,"nonce":"MMFvj/PRBzgnJXIfDgFUvcPg/Do=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOJl1IZM59SixPzlLYAlU"},"target":"b562f1de10a57ace1c970ce44bcade4ce9f4dea8f5f6bf1dcc4a90df37e4f255","message":"I am not sure to call it an \"issue\", but I rather wanted to try to help other users who face this...\n\nSince the screen recorder app \"[Kap](https://getkap.co/)\" is detected as a new window it get's applied to the current layout. Therefor it can (especially when using `tiles`) get hardly possible to screen capture properly, since Kap is designed to overlay on top of all current windows and the user should define an area/window/fullscreen to capture.\nSo f.e. it can look something like this:\n![image](https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/assets/24993816/260b6553-41c6-4670-80c6-93c50af128fb)\n\nWorkaround that work's for me: adding `[[on-window-detected]]` rule\n```toml\n[[on-window-detected]]\nif.app-id = 'com.wulkano.kap'\nrun = 'layout floating'\n```\n\nWhen using this addition in the config it looks (and works) like this:\n![image](https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/assets/24993816/c5586281-e2ef-4bab-ba04-e5d903f6271f)\n\n- AeroSpace version: 0.8.2-Beta\n- macOS version: 14.2.1","files":null}]}